EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to vehicles; providing that vehicles owned by a
charter school of the State are exempt from fees for
registration; and providing other matters properly relating
thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Existing law exempts vehicles owned by the United States, the State of Nevada,
2 any political subdivision of the State or any county, municipal corporation, city,
3 unincorporated town or school district in the State from fees for registration. (NRS
4 482.503) This bill clarifies that vehicles owned by a charter school of the State are
5 exempt from fees for registration.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 482.503 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 482.503 The registration fee imposed by this chapter does not
3 apply to vehicles owned by [the] :
4 1. The United States [, the] ;
5 2. The State of Nevada, [any] including, without limitation, a
6 charter school;
7 3. Any political subdivision of the State of Nevada ; [,] or [any]
8 4. Any county, municipal corporation, city, unincorporated
9 town or school district in the State of Nevada.
